$ s$^{-1}$). The maximum value of total\nradiative losses is reached around the flare peak time, and can go up to 175 kW\nm$^{-2}$ for a single pixel located at footpoint. After a small parameter\nstudy, we find the best model-data consistency in terms of the amplitude of\nradiative losses and the overall atmospheric structure with a RADYN flare\nsimulation in the injected energy flux of $5\\times10^{10}$ erg s$^{-1}$\ncm$^{-2}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 6 Jul 2022 17:54:53 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 25 Aug 2022 15:34:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-07"}
