i slightly larger than the class of ${\\mathbb\nE}$-isometries) to which any ${\\mathbb E}$-contraction can be lifted, and (iii)\nwe use our functional model to recover an earlier result on the existence and\nuniqueness of a ${\\mathbb E}$-isometric lift $(V_1, V_2, V_3)$ of a special\ntype for a ${\\mathbb E}$-contraction $(A,B,T)$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 7 Jul 2022 11:25:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-07-08"}
